This derivative ("buch-paraglidable") is an independent teaching and practice
project accompanying the German book "Softwaremodernisierung mit KI"
(subtitle: "Mit Golden Master, Charakterisierungstests und kleinen
Schritten vom Altsystem zur Zielarchitektur") by Ralf Balz. It is NOT affiliated with or endorsed by
the original Paraglidable project or its author.

The full Git history of the original project has been preserved in this
repository as attribution.

Planned/ongoing substantial modifications (GPLv3 section 5(a) notice — see
the Git history for exact dates and details of each change):

  * Port of the C++/Qt 5 map tiler to Python (numpy/Pillow)
  * Port of the Apache/PHP web layer to Python (FastAPI)
  * Replacement of cron-based scheduling with an in-process Python scheduler
  * Introduction of PostgreSQL for forecast results and metadata
    (large binary data remains file-based)
  * Dependency pinning, containerization rework, tests and CI
  * A visible notice in the web front-end marking this instance as an
    independent re-implementation (added 2026-07-11); a full visual
    redesign establishing a distinct identity is planned (stage F)
  * Front-end identity cleanup (stage F part 1, 2026-07-12): the original
    author's Google Analytics tracking was removed; links pointing to the
    original author (donation, social media, contact, app store, v2) were
    removed or replaced by links to the operator of this instance; the
    GPLv3 attribution notice in the footer remains
  * The web user interface was translated from English to German
    (2026-07-12); the English attribution notice in the footer and the
    license credits were left unchanged
  * Distinct visual identity (2026-07-12): OpenTopoMap base map (with
    attribution), own color scheme (pine/amber), own logo and favicons
    replacing the original ones, project tagline in the header

